																		Black As Night: Part 6
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stormbreath" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3075960); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3075960&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610175132" alt="stormbreath" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3075960)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stormbreath" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3075960); return false;" >stormbreath</a></span> <span class="odate time_1550189998 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">15 Feb 2019 00:19</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4153922">
									

<p>Happy <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saint_Valentine%27s_Day_Massacre">Valentine's Day</a>.</p>
<p>This is the final installment of Black as Night, and the conclusion to my series about Mr. Night.</p>
<p>britishoccult.png is sourced from <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Royal_arms_of_the_United_Kingdom_(print).png">here</a> and is public domain. uiu.png was made by Zhange, and used with her permission.</p>
<p>Thanks to my critters: PeppersGhost, KindlyTurtleClem, ihp, rounderhouse, DrChandra, and Kakroom.</p>
<p>Some notes:</p>
<ul>
<li>UTE-7311-Disco-Beige is Leggy, the greatest bootlegger the Chicago Spirit/Spectre has ever seen. He's mentioned in Spirit Stories, and is the only other shared member of the two groups.</li>
<li>Night's activities in the Wanderer's Library in 1984 are a reference to the curent SCP rp, Origins. Mr. Night is, at time of writing, the focus of an arc involving him staging a takeover of sorts on the Wanderer's Library.</li>
<li>Normally criminals on the FBI Top 10 Most Wanted are caught rather quickly. The UIU Top 13 list is secret, so they don't get the main benefit of public awareness that the Top 10 does. Thus, Mr. Night has been on the list since it's inception.</li>
<li>The prototype weapon that Mr. Night stole from the Pentagram here showed up in Contract Negotiations - he used it to shoot the Investor, but it didn't do much.</li>
<li>Mr. Night got what he wanted out of the Hy-Brasil heist.</li>
<li>The Golden Horde showing up when they did was not a coincidence. It was a small price to pay for being able to escape.</li>
</ul>

